            <title>[JCR-1494] [PATCH] XPathQueryBuilder reports misleading column numbers for faulty queries</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1494</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>XPathQueryBuilder returns an error string with the column offset where a parsing error occurred. Unfortunately this value is difficult to correlate to the users query string, as XPathQueryBuilder embellishes the query by doing&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
statement = &amp;quot;for $v in &amp;quot; + statement + &amp;quot; return $v&amp;quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This patch appends the modified statement to the query message so that the user can get the real position of the error.</description>
